title: Outsole for a shoe

claims.preamble: I claim the ornamental design for an outsole for a shoe, as shown and described.

description: FIG. 1 is a bottom perspective view of an outsole for a shoe showing my new design;
FIG. 2 is a bottom view thereof;
FIG. 3 is a left side view thereof;
FIG. 4 is a right side view thereof;
FIG. 5 is a front view thereof;
FIG. 6 is a rear view thereof; and,
FIG. 7 is an enlarged detail view of the area indicated as 7 in FIG. 1.

The broken line showing an oval shape and curved strip in the arch area of FIGS. 1 & 2, along with the parallel broken lines around the periphery of FIGS. 2–7, represent the boundaries of the design; with neither the lines themselves, nor the areas within them forming any part of the claim.
